SIMPLE: evermore
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Evermore
<hw>Ev`er*more"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>During eternity;
always; forever; for an indefinite period; at all times; -- often used
substantively with <xex>for</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Seek the Lord . . . Seek his face <qex>evermore</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Ps. cv. 4.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And, behold, I am alive for <qex>evermore</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Rev.
i. 18.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Which flow from the presence of God for <qex>evermore</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Tillotson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I <qex>evermore</qex> did love you, Hermia.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Evernic</ent>⟦br⟧
